main event: On 6 March 1966, Trenton police officers received a report of a UFO sighting, observing a large luminous object hovering above a field.
interesting points: The object was described as circular in shape with small bluish lights on the exterior., It remained visible for approximately 1.5 hours and was seen by a large number of citizens., No noise or exhaust gases were observed from the object., The officers failed to communicate or make contact with the object., The object accelerated rapidly at the end of the sighting and disappeared from view.
witness description: large number of citizens observed the object
